<!--Antagningsprov KMH-->
<div class="container white-container col-xs-12">
	<h3>Admission Test</h3>
	<p>This is an ongoing project ordered from the <%= link_to("Royal College of Music", "http://www.kmh.se/", :class => "bold") %> in Stockholm for our course in Interaction. We are a team of five people looking into how to digitalize an admission test. Difficulties are how to input notes, chords and other music related things without making it too complicated for us to implement. We are currently using the following libraries:  AngularJS, VexFlow, BootStrap, Web MIDI, HTML 5 Audio and SASS.</p>
	<div style="text-align: center;">
	  <%= image_tag('KMH.png', :class => "img-responsive", :style => "max-height: 110px; display:inline;") %>
	</div>
</div>


<!--Webshop-->
<div class="container white-container col-xs-12">
	<h3>Web shop</h3>
	<p>For the course in web security I was the project leader in a project where we were to develop a fictional web shop. The main objective was to take in consideration as many security issues as possible while developing the site. We used php, bootstrap and a MySQL database on an Apache server. </p>
	<div style="text-align: center;">
	  <%= image_tag('webshop.png', :class => "img-responsive", :style => "max-height: 400px; display:inline;") %>
	</div>
</div>

<!--Nilex-->
