<!--Lundakarnevalen-->
<div class="container white-container col-xs-12">
	<h3>Web developer for Lundakarnevalen</h3>
	<p><%= link_to("Lundakarnevalen", "http://www.lundakarnevalen.se/", :class => "bold") %> is a recurring carneval in Lund produced by students at the university, it is probably the biggest event in Lund. During this project I learned a lot about Ruby on Rails. It was my first project developing for a large scale website. For me this was mostly back-end development which was a good learning experience. My main contribution was in developing a warehouse and order system. Tools used were Ruby on Rails development environment, Twitter Bootstrap for visuals, Heroku for deployment where a Unicorn web server was running and an SQLite database. I have borrowed some of the css used in this project for my own website.</p>
	<div style="text-align: center;">
	  <%= image_tag('karnevalist.png', :class => "img-responsive", :style => "max-height: 400px; display:inline;") %>
